HEADWORD: Stingbull
<hw>Sting"bull`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The European greater weever fish (<spn>Trachinus draco</spn>),
which is capable of inflicting severe wounds with the spinous rays of
its dorsal fin. See <er>Weever</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stinger</ent>⟦br⟧
